<paragraph blockId="37.[189,334,267,293]" box="[189,334,267,293]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,334,267,293]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,334,267,293]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="37.[189,1399,314,1009]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
Rhizomatous, erect, monoecious herb, 
<quantity box="[635,758,314,340]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" unit="cm" value="40.0" valueMax="60.0" valueMin="20.0">20â€“60 cm</quantity>
. Rhizome: ca 
<quantity box="[916,982,314,341]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" unit="mm" value="5.0">5 mm</quantity>
wide, pubescent, internodes 
<quantity box="[1311,1399,314,340]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" unit="cm" value="2.0" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="1.0">1â€“3 cm</quantity>
long. Stem: stout, ca 
<quantity box="[449,521,349,376]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" unit="mm" value="5.0">5 mm</quantity>
wide, pubescent, internodes 
<quantity box="[873,979,349,376]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" metricValueMax="1.8" metricValueMin="0.7" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" unit="cm" value="12.5" valueMax="18.0" valueMin="7.0">7â€“18 cm</quantity>
long. Stipules: broadly lanceolate, 10â€“15 Ã— 
<quantity box="[295,401,384,411]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" unit="mm" value="4.0" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="3.0">3â€“5 mm</quantity>
, puberulous, persistent. Leaves: petiole 4â€“10(â€“18) cm long, pubescent; lamina ovate, basifixed, base cordate with lobes not overlapping, 5â€“20(â€“30) Ã— 5â€“15(â€“20) cm, asymmetric, upper surface green with a darker centre, sparsely hispid or glabrous, underside red-purple, pubescent to puberulous mostly on the veins, venation palmate, midrib 4â€“15(â€“25) cm long; margin acutely deeply lobed, dentate with finer serration, with sparse hairs; apex acute. Inflorescence: cymose, axillary, several; peduncle pilose, branching up to three times, primary 
<quantity box="[933,1039,560,587]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="0.5" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" unit="cm" value="10.0" valueMax="15.0" valueMin="5.0">5â€“15 cm</quantity>
long, secondary 
<quantity box="[1243,1338,560,587]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" unit="cm" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2â€“3 cm</quantity>
long and tertiary 
<quantity box="[328,430,595,622]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" unit="mm" value="5.0" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="4.0">4â€“6 mm</quantity>
long, with 3â€“ 
<specimenCount box="[593,696,595,622]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" type="female">4 female</specimenCount>
flowers and 2â€“ 
<specimenCount box="[879,956,595,622]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" type="male">3 male</specimenCount>
flowers; bracts not seen. Male flower: pedicel 
<quantity box="[286,424,631,657]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" unit="mm" value="25.0" valueMax="30.0" valueMin="20.0">20 â€“30 mm</quantity>
long, pubescent; tepals 4; outer tepals ovate-orbicular, (6â€“)10â€“15 Ã— 
<quantity box="[1286,1394,631,657]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" unit="mm" value="5.5" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="4.0">4â€“7 mm</quantity>
, yellow, tomentose on reverse, margin entire; inner tepals obovate, 8â€“12 Ã— 
<quantity box="[1075,1183,666,692]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" unit="mm" value="3.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="3.0">3â€“4 mm</quantity>
, yellow, glabrous; androecium with 40â€“60 stamens, symmetric; filaments 
<quantity box="[835,953,701,728]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" unit="mm" value="1.25" valueMax="1.5" valueMin="1.0">1â€“1.5 mm</quantity>
long, fused at the base; anther ellipticglobose, 
<quantity box="[297,400,736,763]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" unit="mm" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1â€“2 mm</quantity>
long, dehiscing through slits longer than half the length of the anther, not hooded, connective extended. Female flower: pedicel 
<quantity box="[738,856,771,798]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.15" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="0.8" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" unit="mm" value="11.5" valueMax="15.0" valueMin="8.0">8â€“15 mm</quantity>
long, pubescent; bracteoles absent; tepals 5, equal, broadly ovate to oblong, outer tepals 10â€“13 Ã— 
<quantity box="[823,942,806,833]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" unit="mm" value="7.5" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="5.0">5â€“10 mm</quantity>
, yellow, tomentose on reverse, margin entire, inner tepals smaller and glabrous; ovary 2-locular, placentae bifid; capsule ellipsoid, tomentose, with one long rounded oblong wing and two short triangular wings; styles 3, deeply forked once and twisted once, persistent. Fruit: recurved; capsule ellipsoid, 5â€“7 Ã— 
<quantity box="[993,1103,912,939]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" unit="mm" value="5.0" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="4.0">4â€“6 mm</quantity>
, short tomentose; wings extending along the pedicel slightly, unequal; longest round oblong with crenate tip, 6â€“12 Ã— 
<quantity box="[1287,1394,948,974]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" unit="mm" value="3.0" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="2.0">2â€“4 mm</quantity>
; shortest triangular, 1â€“2 Ã— 
<quantity box="[493,599,983,1009]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" unit="mm" value="3.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="3.0">3â€“4 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
